<?xml version="1.0"?>
<package xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <metadata>
    <id>calibre</id>
    <title>Calibre</title>
    <version>1.9.0</version>
    <authors>Kovid Goyal</authors>
    <owners>Gary Ewan Park</owners>
    <summary>calibre is the one stop solution to all your e-book needs.</summary>
    <description>calibre is a free and open source e-book library management application developed by users of e-books for users of e-books.</description>
    <projectUrl>http://calibre-ebook.com/</projectUrl>
    <tags>ebook library management</tags>
    <copyright>Kovid Goyal</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.ico</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: Drivers for the new Nook Glowlight, Lenovo IdeaPad and Kindle Fire HDX (linux)
    - New: Add an option to check for duplicates (books with the same title/author) when copying between libraries. Option is under Preferences - Adding books.
	- New: Content server: Display book title on details page. Also put the most important fields (authors/series/tags) at the top.
	- New: When developing recipes using the command line, allow specifying the number of feeds and articles when using the --test parameter.
	- New: PDF Output: Option to control title of generated Table of Contents
	- New: PDF metadata: If one of the keywords in the PDF is a valid ISBN, use it as the ISBN for the book
	- Fixed: Amazon metadata download: Fix spurious ratings being returned for unrated books.
	- Fixed: Bulk metadata edit: Only clear series if the clear series checkbox is checked. Also add a clear checkbox for publishers, so that publishers can be removed.
	- Fixed: Use h2 tag for the inserted Table of Contents title for the MOBI and PDF formats as well as the EPUB and AZW3 formats.
	- Fixed: Fix comments editor in review metadata becoming too small on small screens.
	- Fixed: DOCX Input: Fix hyperlink showing as underlined even if the hyperlink style in word is set to not show underlines.
	- Fixed: E-book viewer: Remember the size of the 'Inspect' window used to examine the book's code.
	- Fixed: Wireless driver: Fix bug that prevented different formats of the same book on the device from being recognized
	- Fixed: Bulk metadata download: When downloading only covers and some covers fail, do not show the failed books while reviewing downloaded metadata.
	- Fixed: BibTeX catalogs: Strip unmatched braces to prevent generation of invalid .bib file.
    - Improved News Source: Reuters (Japan)
	- Improved News Source: MIT Technology Review
	- Improved News Source: dotNet Magazine
	- Improved News Source: Science Based News
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
